Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario:

## 1. Windows-only tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)] // MSTest v3+ with Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.OS
public void Registry_ReadsValue() { ... }

// Or manually:
[TestMethod]
public void Registry_ReadsValue()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
    // ...
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void Render_UsesGPU() { ... }

// Filter in CI: dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"

// Or conditionally at runtime:
[TestMethod]
public void Render_UsesGPU()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");
    // ...
}
```

## 3. Flaky external API — retry with `[TestMethod]`

```csharp
// MSTest v3.8+: built-in retry
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void Weather_ReturnsForecast() { ... }
```

## 4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup() => _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();

    [TestCleanup] // runs even if the test fails or throws
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void WritesToTempFile()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
    }
}
```

**Summary:** Use `[TestCategory]` + filters or `Assert.Inconclusive` for conditional skipping, `[Retry(n)]` for flaky tests, and `[TestCleanup]` for guaranteed teardown.
